node.text:
Photo by @shingaridavesh
•
Glacier NP is among my top 5 National Parks (of 35+ I have visited). It’s landscape resembles the Canadian Rockies and is so unique and so peaceful. I was lucky to spot a Grizzly and her 2 cubs during my visit. 🐻 🐻

Photo by @rastarunner_ 
PC: @gabsthegreat_

Over the years, I’ve created a handful of life rules that I live by…⁣
⁣
1. I’m never too busy to stop and pet the puppies.⁣
⁣
2. I’ll never turn down a good cookie.⁣
⁣
And if I’m running to a lake, no matter what, I’m jumping in 😆⁣

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Glacier_National_Park 🦋 on July 07, 2021 tagging @glaciernps, and @jchnpaul. May be an image of lake, nature and mountain.

node.text:
Photo & video by @jchnpaul
•
This lake was on my short list of places to see while in Glacier.  It is not very convenient to get to however. Twenty miles of unmaintained roads and not a whole lot else to see close to it. So we put it off until I was sure I’d have to wait until another trip here to see it. We were on the opposite side of the park as far north as we could be and Felicia changed her flight plans to extend her stay in the park. “Where to now?” she asked. I knew right where we were going. Five hours of driving that day around the entire perimeter of Glacier because of closed roads (ie Road to the Sun). We missed our turn and nearly crossed into Canada. But we found it and it was everything I hoped it would be. 
•
#bowmanlake 
•••
••
•
